docs/asset-charter.md:128:| skill:adversarial-review-loop | CORE | Dual-track Codex×Claude review + 13-dim codebase improvement loop engine (branch/codebase/multi-agent 3 modes + lifecycle mode) | ① | branch-PR diff or repo tree → both-approve verdict / score-state.json + contracts + merged quality/* branches | "adversarial review"/"quality loop"/--multi-agent/--lifecycle triggers; former pm-quality-harness-loop and /quality-loop entry are absorbed here | Only dual-review + contract-fan-out engine in the plugin. quality-eval supplies the rubric (data, not engine); lifecycle mode wraps the sequencing/harness-doc-sync/merge tail. Supersession of quality-eval as ENTRY POINT is claimed but quality-eval stays the rubric SoT (data vs engine split). |
docs/asset-charter.md:131:| skill:diagnosing-llm-output-leaks | MERGED | Triage map: classify LLM output token leaks as data-layer / prompt / stochastic / bilingual-gap before iterating prompts a 3rd time | ① | N≥10 fresh samples + pattern-scanner aggregates → leak class + correct fix surface (builder vs prompt vs ignore) | manual, when prompt-level leak fixes are not converging; no hook/script wiring | Only LLM-leak triage asset; diagnosing-stale-runtime covers runtime-vs-source mismatch — disjoint symptom class. quality-eval dim 12 scores prompt quality but does not diagnose leaks. → MERGED into `diagnosing` (llm-output-leaks mode) 2026-06-07. |
docs/asset-charter.md:133:| skill:diagnosing | CORE | Dual-mode diagnostic skill: llm-output-leaks (classify LLM token leaks before iterating prompts a 3rd time) + stale-runtime (dead-or-alive verdicts for removed-code-still-runs symptoms); absorbed diagnosing-llm-output-leaks + diagnosing-stale-runtime 2026-06-07 | ① | MODE llm-output-leaks: N≥10 samples + pattern-scanner → leak class + correct fix surface. MODE stale-runtime: symptom → ordered evidence checks → verified dead/alive verdict | manual, when prompt-level fixes not converging or code removal not taking effect; subcommand-routed (skills/diagnosing/SKILL.md) | Only asset covering both LLM-output-leak classification and runtime-state dead-or-alive verdicts; residue-audit owns deletion gate, quality-eval scores prompt quality — disjoint surfaces. Modes share one SKILL.md but zero code overlap. |
docs/asset-charter.md:136:| skill:pm-quality-harness-loop | ABSORBED | Superset lifecycle orchestrator: CI-gate-faithfulness-first → dim fan-out → adversarial bug-hunt → harness-doc sync → honest DoD → autonomous merge tail | ①②④ | repo → measurably-better + correctness-verified + docs-synced + merged repo, with real (non-round-number) weighted score | "big-tech 95"/"quality lift then merge"/"harden and ship" phrasings; explicitly composes ARL + quality-eval + doc-management | Cites-not-duplicates the ARL engine; unique value = sequencing + Phase 0 CI-faithfulness + Phase 3 harness-doc-sync + merge tail, none of which ARL has. Thin orchestration layer → uniqueness 7. → ABSORBED into adversarial-review-loop --lifecycle mode 2026-06-07 (13 capabilities, zero loss). |
docs/asset-charter.md:137:| skill:quality-eval | CORE | 13-dimension big-tech rubric SoT — weights, hard-fail caps, penalty calibration, anti-inflation guard, score-state.json schema | ①④ | any codebase (auto language detect / .quality-loop.json) → per-dim scores + weighted total → .planning/quality/score-state.json + eval-report | standalone "quality eval"/"score this project"; consumed by ARL codebase EVALUATE (../quality-eval/SKILL.md fed to Codex track), ARL lifecycle mode, and swarm `bench` scoring | Sole rubric definition — ARL lifecycle/codebase and swarm bench cite it rather than restating dims. Its standalone TRIGGER surface collides with ARL codebase-mode triggers (ARL claims to supersede it as entry) — keep as rubric SoT, Standalone entry triggers removed 2026-06-07 — ARL codebase mode is the sole entry; this stays rubric data SoT. |
docs/asset-charter.md:138:| skill:residue-audit | KEEP | Semantic code-residue audit linters can't block on — dead code / diverged duplicates / stale comments / orphan artifacts via parallel read-only fan-out + 6-gate + FP catalog, report-first | ①④ | green-baseline repo + deterministic-tool seed (ruff/vulture/jscpd) → ranked P0/P1/P2 table with 6-gate column + FALSE-POSITIVE(keep) list → approval-gated category-batched PRs | "residue audit"/"dead code purge"/"잔재 제거" phrasings; post-refactor/migration | Only semantic dead-code/dedup asset; explicitly fences off doc-management AUDIT (doc prose), ARL (quality scoring), setup-harness (bootstrap). references/six-gate.md + false-positive-catalog.md both exist. |
docs/asset-charter.md:142:| skill:swarm-bench | ABSORBED | 3-arm benchmark — same task via full swarm vs claude-solo vs codex-solo, each scored by quality-eval, comparison report | ① | task description (+--repeats N) → .planning/autopilot/bench/<epoch>/report.md with score/time/tokens per arm | "swarm bench"/"is swarm better than codex"; runs swarm/scripts/bench.sh | Empirical-comparison behavior now lives as swarm `bench` subcommand. Reuses quality-eval rubric — consumer, not duplicator. bench.sh verified present. → ABSORBED into swarm `bench` subcommand 2026-06-07. |
